  "content": "\u003cp\u003eDoes anyone else think REST is overrated?\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhy are we pretending that everything has to conform to a small handful of verbs? I can\u0026#39;t tell you how many times I\u0026#39;ve had the exact same conversation about PUT vs POST. If it\u0026#39;s all made up then we should pick better names.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eREST doesn\u0026#39;t handle streaming use cases at all.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eREST doesn\u0026#39;t do errors well. If you want a user readable description you have to make up your own format. Many other protocols include an error code and a customizable error message.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe\u0026#39;ve essentially built SOAP again with OpenAPI and jsonschema. JSON is inefficient and WHY CAN\u0026#39;T I HAVE TRAILING COMMAS?? Sorry, I got carried away. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI just think we are attaching extra technology on top of problems instead of considering alternative approaches. It\u0026#39;s bandaids all the way down.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe can do better than REST\u003c/p\u003e",
